data.title: Central Jersey athletes to watch, fall 2024: The top returning non-football players
data.meta_description: The top non-football playing athletes to watch for the fall 2024 high school sports season in Central Jersey
data.text:
As the calendar turns to August, we are just weeks away from the fall varsity season in the Skyland Conference, Greater Middlesex Conference and western Union County.

Here are the top players in each sport expected to return for the 2024 campaign.

More: Ready for the Olympics? Our guide to NJ athletes headed to the 2024 Summer Games

More: 'Good memories': Colonia's Ben LaSala retires after 43 years as coach and administrator
